goals.question: What is the distribution of boroughs by longitude?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of boroughs across the longitude axis of London. We can identify any outliers or clusters of boroughs.

goals.question: What is the distribution of boroughs by latitude?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of boroughs across the latitude axis of London. We can identify any outliers or clusters of boroughs.

goals.question: Which borough has the highest longitude value?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of cx field sorted in descending order
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the borough with the highest longitude value. We can also compare the longitude values of different boroughs.

goals.question: Which borough has the highest latitude value?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of cy field sorted in descending order
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the borough with the highest latitude value. We can also compare the latitude values of different boroughs.

goals.question: Is there any correlation between longitude and latitude values of boroughs?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of cx and cy fields
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any correlation between the longitude and latitude values of boroughs. We can also identify any outliers or clusters of boroughs.

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='cx', kde=False)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of boroughs by longitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='cy', kde=False)
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of boroughs by latitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='name', y='cx', data=data, order=data.sort_values('cx', ascending=False).name)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.axhline(data.cx.max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Maximum longitude value: {data.cx.max():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.title('Which borough has the highest longitude value?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sorted_data = data.sort_values(by='cy', ascending=False)
    ax = sns.barplot(x='name', y='cy', data=sorted_data)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which borough has the highest latitude value?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(sorted_data['cy'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Max Latitude: {sorted_data['cy'].max():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
